# Frontend Layout Architecture Rules

**Reference**: See `/docs/technical/FRONTEND_LAYOUT_ARCHITECTURE.md` for complete architecture documentation.

## Core Principles

### 1. URL as Source of Truth for Navigation

**❌ WRONG**: Storing route/tab state separately from URL
```javascript
// Don't do this
const state = {
  activeTab: 'chat',
  currentRoute: '/chat'
};
```

**✅ CORRECT**: Derive navigation state from URL
```javascript
// Derive from URL
function getActiveTab() {
  const route = window.location.pathname;
  return routeToTabMap[route] || 'chat';
}

// Update URL to navigate
function navigateToRoute(route) {
  window.history.pushState({}, '', route);
  // Components react to URL change
}
```

**Rules**:
- Never store `activeTab` or `currentRoute` in component state
- Always derive navigation state from `window.location.pathname` or `window.location.hash`
- Use `window.history.pushState()` or router library to navigate
- Listen for `popstate` events to handle browser back/forward

### 2. Portal Root for All Overlays

**❌ WRONG**: Rendering modals/tooltips inside component DOM
```javascript
// Don't do this - modal inherits parent stacking context
function showModal() {
  const modal = document.createElement('div');
  this.container.appendChild(modal); // Wrong!
}
```

**✅ CORRECT**: Render all overlays in portal root
```javascript
// Portal root must exist in HTML
// <div id="portal-root"></div>

function createPortal(element, targetId = 'portal-root') {
  const portalRoot = document.getElementById(targetId) || createPortalRoot(targetId);
  return portalRoot.appendChild(element);
}

function showModal(content) {
  const modal = document.createElement('div');
  modal.style.zIndex = 'var(--z-modal)';
  createPortal(modal); // Renders in portal-root
}
```

**Rules**:
- All modals, tooltips, dropdowns, notifications must render in `#portal-root`
- Never append overlays to component containers
- Use z-index tokens: `--z-modal`, `--z-tooltip`, `--z-dropdown`, etc.
- Portal root must exist in HTML: `<div id="portal-root"></div>`

### 3. State Boundaries

**Layout State** (managed by LayoutStore):
- Sidebar visibility/collapse
- Mobile menu state
- Theme preference
- Responsive breakpoint detection

**Page State** (managed by page components):
- Page-specific data (conversations, executions, etc.)
- Page loading states
- Page filters/search

**Feature State** (managed by feature components):
- Component-specific UI state
- Form inputs
- Component interactions

**Rules**:
- State lives at the lowest level that needs it
- Only lift state up when multiple components need it
- Layout state ≠ Page state ≠ Feature state
- Don't mix concerns across boundaries

### 4. Component Structure

**Framework-Agnostic**: Components can be vanilla JS, React, Vue, etc. Follow these patterns:

**Vanilla JavaScript**:
```javascript
class Component {
  constructor(element, options) {
    this.element = element;
    this.state = {};
    this.init();
  }
  
  render() { /* DOM manipulation */ }
  destroy() { /* Cleanup */ }
}
```

**React**:
```typescript
function Component({ props }) {
  const [state, setState] = useState({});
  useEffect(() => { return () => cleanup(); }, []);
  return <div>...</div>;
}
```

**Rules**:
- Components must have clear lifecycle: init → render → destroy/cleanup
- Use consistent naming: `ComponentName` for classes/components
- Keep components focused on single responsibility
- Document component API (props, state, methods)

### 5. Z-Index Layering

Use consistent z-index tokens:
```css
--z-base: 0;
--z-elevated: 10;
--z-sticky: 20;
--z-dropdown: 30;
--z-overlay: 40;
--z-modal: 50;
--z-tooltip: 60;
--z-notification: 70;
```

**Rules**:
- Never use arbitrary z-index values (e.g., `z-index: 9999`)
- Use CSS custom properties for z-index
- All overlays in portal root use these tokens
- Sticky elements use `--z-sticky`

## File Structure

Follow this structure:
```
dashboard/
├── components/
│   ├── layout/        # AppShell, Header, Navigation, Sidebar, ContentArea
│   ├── pages/         # ChatPage, OverviewPage, etc.
│   ├── features/      # ConversationList, MessageList, etc.
│   └── primitives/    # Button, Card, Modal, Badge, etc.
├── stores/
│   └── layout-store.js  # Layout state management
├── utils/
│   ├── routing.js      # Route utilities (derive from URL)
│   └── portal.js       # Portal rendering utilities
└── styles/
    └── tokens.css      # Design tokens (z-index, colors, spacing)
```

## Common Mistakes to Avoid

1. **Duplicate route state**: Don't store route in state when URL already has it
2. **Overlays in wrong DOM**: Don't render modals inside component trees
3. **Mixed state concerns**: Don't put page data in layout state
4. **Arbitrary z-index**: Don't use `z-index: 9999` - use tokens
5. **Framework lock-in**: Keep components framework-agnostic where possible

## Verification Checklist

When implementing components, verify:
- [ ] Navigation state derived from URL, not stored separately
- [ ] Overlays render in `#portal-root`, not component DOM
- [ ] State boundaries respected (layout vs page vs feature)
- [ ] Z-index uses tokens, not arbitrary values
- [ ] Components have clear lifecycle (init/render/destroy)
- [ ] Portal root exists in HTML
